</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Commonly, the file names were: wines.dll, winsec.dll, rdmgr.dll, tcpsys.dll, svcmgr.dll, rnamsvc.dll, httpcmgr.dll, icmpsec.dll and netmag.dll.</p>
<p>Table 1 shows the confirmed cases of attacks.</p>
