<p class="centered-caption">Table 3: Decoy files disguised as legitimate files.</p>
<p>The file names used in the Escad variant are: adobe.exe, AdobeArm.exe, AdobeFlash.exe, msdtc.exe and msnconf.exe.</p>
<p>Following the <em>Sony Pictures</em> hack in November 2014, Operation Red Dot started to persistently attack the defence industry and government institutions of South Korea, beginning in spring 2015.</p>
